OL,3,CGloucestershire Constabulary
OL,4,C'inadequate' at tackling organised
OL,5,Ccrime
OL,7,FIn addition, the report found the
OL,8,Fforce was not always allocating cases
OL,9,Frelated to modern slavery and human
OL,10,Ftrafficking for investigation - and
OL,11,Fthat this was due to some teams not
OL,12,Fhaving the right experience and others
OL,13,Flacking capacity.
OL,15,FGloucestershire Police's response
OL,17,FAccording to Assistant Chief Constable
OL,18,FRich Ocone, the report did not
OL,19,F"represent(s) how (the force is)
OL,20,Ftackling serious and organised crime."
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/7
